motions.motion_text:
WHEREAS the 2026 Update to Local Priority Rules under the Housing Services Act, 2011 indicates that more than 16,000 households are currently waiting for a Rent‑Geared‑to‑Income (RGI) housing offer, and confirms that local rules governing access and ongoing eligibility must remain current, responsive, transparent, and accountable to community needs and public resources;
WHEREAS in its role as Service Manager under the Housing Services Act, the City has delegated the management of the RGI Centralized Waiting List (CWL) and Affordable Housing Waiting List (AHWL) to The Social Housing Registry of Ottawa (The Registry) and the City exclusively funds the Registry as administrator of the RGI CWL and AHWL.
WHEREAS the City, in partnership with The Registry and Community Housing Providers, are in the process of implementing the Integrated Housing System (IHS), to modernize and digitize The Registry’s business processes.
WHEREAS the IHS system is intended to support service enhancements for Registry applications, allowing clients to both submit applications and track the status of their file online.
WHEREAS the update to business practices that is underway presents an opportunity to review and improve The Registry’s operations to ensure they are best positioned to support Ottawa residents, recognizing increasing demands for affordable housing in the community;
THEREFORE BE IT RESOLVED that staff be directed to undertake a detailed review of The Registry to ensure that the RGI CWL and AHWL accurately reflect current housing needs, and that The Registry’s services are delivered in an accountable manner that maximizes value for the City, clients, and Community Housing Providers and improves flow for those waiting for homes;
AND BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the review include, but not be limited to:
AND BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that staff report back with findings, financial implications, and recommendations to improve accountability, service effectiveness, and cost efficiency — including proposed next steps — by Q2 2027.
